What is FastAPI?
Definition
FastAPI is a modern Python web framework used to build APIs quickly and efficiently.
It is designed for:
High performance
Automatic API documentation
Type safety
Easy development
Why are we using FastAPI?
Because our application needs a backend that can:
Receive user requests
Call the LLM
Generate quizzes
Save user progress
Retrieve knowledge
Communicate with the frontend
FastAPI is well-suited for all of these.
What is a Backend?
A backend is software that runs on a server and processes requests from clients.
Responsibilities include:
Business logic
Database interaction
Authentication
Calling external APIs (like an LLM)
What is an API Endpoint?
An endpoint is a specific URL that performs a particular action.
Example:
GET /health
Returns the application's health status.
POST /learn
Explains an AI concept.
POST /quiz
Generates a quiz.


