What is Uvicorn?
Answer:
Uvicorn is an ASGI server that runs FastAPI applications. It receives HTTP requests from clients, passes them to the FastAPI application, and returns HTTP responses.



FastAPI Swagger UI (OpenAPI Documentation)
What is Swagger UI?
Definition
Swagger UI is an automatically generated, interactive web interface that documents and allows testing of REST APIs.
FastAPI automatically creates Swagger UI based on your API code.
By default, it is available at:
http://localhost:8000/docs
Why is Swagger UI useful?
Swagger UI allows developers to:
View all available API endpoints
Understand request and response formats
Test APIs without writing frontend code
Verify backend functionality during development
It acts as an interactive API playground.
How does FastAPI generate Swagger UI?
When FastAPI starts:
Python Code
      │
      ▼
FastAPI
      │
      ▼
OpenAPI Specification
      │
      ▼
Swagger UI
FastAPI reads your endpoint definitions and automatically creates an OpenAPI specification, which Swagger UI uses to render interactive documentation.
Example
Suppose you define:
@app.get("/")
def home():
    return {"message": "Welcome"}
Swagger UI automatically displays:
GET /

Response:
{
    "message": "Welcome"
}
without requiring any manual documentation.
Advantages
Automatic API documentation
Interactive testing interface
Always synchronized with the source code
Reduces manual documentation effort
Useful for frontend and backend collaboration
